{"title_page": "Lydia Fenet", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{short description|American auctioneer and author|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n[[File:Lydia Fenet.jpg|thumb|Lydia Fenet|250px]]\n'''Lydia Fenet''' is an American [[auctioneer]] and author. She is the Global Managing Director of Strategic Partnerships and the lead Benefit Auctioneer at [[Christie\u2019s]] Auction House where she has worked since 1999.\n\n==Early life and education==\nFenet grew up in Lake Charles, Louisiana. She attended boarding school at The Taft School in Watertown, CT and then went to [[Sewanee: The University of the South|Sewanee]] double majoring in art history and history.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gotham Gigs: Lydia Fenet, VP of Christie's |url=https://www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20111113/SUB/311139995/gotham-gigs-lydia-fenet-vp-of-christie-s |website=Crain's New York Business |language=en |date=12 November 2011}}</ref> During that time she participated in the European Studies program at [[Oxford University]].\n\n==Career==\nIn college, Fenet interned for Senator John Breaux in Washington, DC and Sir Julian Brazier in the House of Commons. Between her junior and senior year in college she interned for Christie\u2019s auction house. She returned to the firm immediately after college working in the Special Events department for five years before taking over as Head of Special Events for North and South America.<ref>{{cite web |last1=BLITZER |first1=CAROL ANNE |title=Perfect provenance |url=https://www.theadvocate.com/baton_rouge/entertainment_life/article_ddedcec9-bb9b-503f-9bcc-4e56566a70fe.html |website=The Advocate |language=en}}</ref> In 2011 she launched the Strategic Partnerships division for Christie\u2019s a division which she has scaled to a global division.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sommer |first1=Cari |title=Selling Your Vision And Other Advice From One of Christie's Top Auctioneers |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/carisommer/2018/05/04/advice-from-christies-auctioneer-lydia-fenet-on-selling-your-vision/#e482dbb47404 |website=Forbes |language=en}}</ref> In addition to her role as Global Managing Director of Strategic Partnerships, Fenet is also the lead benefit auctioneer for the firm raising over half a billion dollars for non-profits around the world.<ref>{{cite web |title=See Christie's Auctioneer Lydia Fenet's Favorite Works From artnet Galleries |url=https://news.artnet.com/partner-content/lydia-fenet-explores-artnet-galleries |website=Artnet}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Collins |first1=Glenn |title=Powerhouse Fare for High-Powered Bidders |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/06/27/dining/auction-houses-add-food-and-drink-to-lure-clients.html |website=The New York Times |date=25 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nFenet is also a book author of the best selling book,<ref>{{cite web |title=The Woman Behind the Bestselling Self-Help Book Every Working Woman Should Read |url=https://fashionweekdaily.com/lydia-fenet-the-most-powerful-woman-in-the-room-is-you/ |website=Daily Front Row |date=8 August 2019}}</ref> ''The Most Powerful Woman in the Room is You'' published by [[Simon & Schuster]] in April 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wally |first1=Maxine |title=Lydia Fenet Wrote Her New Book in Under Three Months |url=https://wwd.com/eye/parties/lydia-fenet-new-book-the-most-powerful-woman-in-the-world-is-you-three-months-1203102643/ |website=WWD |language=en |date=10 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Garnett |first1=Laura |title=10 New Books That Will Help You Spring-Clean Your Life |url=https://www.inc.com/laura-garnett/ready-for-spring-these-10-new-books-will-help-you-spring-clean-your-life-now.html |website=Inc.com |date=17 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=We Review Four New Books On Middle Eastern Art, Femininity And Empowerment |url=https://www.harpersbazaararabia.com/art/news/we-review-four-new-books-on-middle-eastern-art |website=Harper's Bazaar |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Cantrell |first1=Liz |title=Want to Command a Room? Ask the Benefit Auctioneer Who Raised Half a Billion Dollars for Nonprofits |url=https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/money-and-power/a27058451/lydia-fenet-most-powerful-woman-in-the-room-is-you/ |website=Town & Country |date=9 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=R. STEPHANIE |first1=BRUNO |title='The Most Powerful Woman in the World is You': Louisiana native, charity auctioneer explains it all in new book |url=https://www.theadvocate.com/baton_rouge/entertainment_life/article_3a24ec38-8ea3-11e9-a676-0f9196153644.html |website=The Advocate |language=en}}</ref> She is a keynote speaker represented by CAA\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fenet, Lydia}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sewanee: The University of the South alumni]]\n[[Category:Female auctioneers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women writers]]\n[[Category:American auctioneers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American women non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American auctioneer and author|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n[[File:Lydia Fenet.jpg|thumb|Lydia Fenet|250px]]\n'''Lydia Fenet''' is an American [[auctioneer]] and author. She is the Global Managing Director of Strategic Partnerships and the lead Benefit Auctioneer at [[Christie\u2019s]] Auction House where she has worked since 1999.\n\n==Early life and education==\nFenet grew up in Lake Charles, Louisiana. She attended boarding school at The Taft School in Watertown, CT and then went to [[Sewanee: The University of the South|Sewanee]] double majoring in art history and history.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gotham Gigs: Lydia Fenet, VP of Christie's |url=https://www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20111113/SUB/311139995/gotham-gigs-lydia-fenet-vp-of-christie-s |website=Crain's New York Business |language=en |date=12 November 2011}}</ref> During that time she participated in the European Studies program at [[Oxford University]].\n\n==Career==\nIn college, Fenet interned for Senator John Breaux in Washington, DC and Sir Julian Brazier in the House of Commons. Between her junior and senior year in college she interned for Christie\u2019s auction house. She returned to the firm immediately after college working in the Special Events department for five years before taking over as Head of Special Events for North and South America.<ref>{{cite web |last1=BLITZER |first1=CAROL ANNE |title=Perfect provenance |url=https://www.theadvocate.com/baton_rouge/entertainment_life/article_ddedcec9-bb9b-503f-9bcc-4e56566a70fe.html |website=The Advocate |language=en}}</ref> In 2011 she launched the Strategic Partnerships division for Christie\u2019s a division which she has scaled to a global division.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sommer |first1=Cari |title=Selling Your Vision And Other Advice From One of Christie's Top Auctioneers |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/carisommer/2018/05/04/advice-from-christies-auctioneer-lydia-fenet-on-selling-your-vision/#e482dbb47404 |website=Forbes |language=en}}</ref> In addition to her role as Global Managing Director of Strategic Partnerships, Fenet is also the lead benefit auctioneer for the firm raising over half a billion dollars for non-profits around the world.<ref>{{cite web |title=See Christie's Auctioneer Lydia Fenet's Favorite Works From artnet Galleries |url=https://news.artnet.com/partner-content/lydia-fenet-explores-artnet-galleries |website=Artnet}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Collins |first1=Glenn |title=Powerhouse Fare for High-Powered Bidders |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/06/27/dining/auction-houses-add-food-and-drink-to-lure-clients.html |website=The New York Times |date=25 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nFenet is also a book author of the best selling book,<ref>{{cite web |title=The Woman Behind the Bestselling Self-Help Book Every Working Woman Should Read |url=https://fashionweekdaily.com/lydia-fenet-the-most-powerful-woman-in-the-room-is-you/ |website=Daily Front Row |date=8 August 2019}}</ref> ''The Most Powerful Woman in the Room is You'' published by [[Simon & Schuster]] in April 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wally |first1=Maxine |title=Lydia Fenet Wrote Her New Book in Under Three Months |url=https://wwd.com/eye/parties/lydia-fenet-new-book-the-most-powerful-woman-in-the-world-is-you-three-months-1203102643/ |website=WWD |language=en |date=10 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Garnett |first1=Laura |title=10 New Books That Will Help You Spring-Clean Your Life |url=https://www.inc.com/laura-garnett/ready-for-spring-these-10-new-books-will-help-you-spring-clean-your-life-now.html |website=Inc.com |date=17 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=We Review Four New Books On Middle Eastern Art, Femininity And Empowerment |url=https://www.harpersbazaararabia.com/art/news/we-review-four-new-books-on-middle-eastern-art |website=Harper's Bazaar |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Cantrell |first1=Liz |title=Want to Command a Room? Ask the Benefit Auctioneer Who Raised Half a Billion Dollars for Nonprofits |url=https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/money-and-power/a27058451/lydia-fenet-most-powerful-woman-in-the-room-is-you/ |website=Town & Country |date=9 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=R. STEPHANIE |first1=BRUNO |title='The Most Powerful Woman in the World is You': Louisiana native, charity auctioneer explains it all in new book |url=https://www.theadvocate.com/baton_rouge/entertainment_life/article_3a24ec38-8ea3-11e9-a676-0f9196153644.html |website=The Advocate |language=en}}</ref> She is a keynote speaker represented by CAA\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fenet, Lydia}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sewanee: The University of the South alumni]]\n[[Category:Female auctioneers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women writers]]\n[[Category:American auctioneers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American women non-ficti